page.title: 13BUSHY PARK, HAMPTON WICK
page.content: {Bushy Park }is a royal park that has been given to the people. It is part of the grounds of Hampton Court Palace. In{Bushy Park}there are lots of different types of animals. There are four hundred deer in the Park, two hundred fallow deer and two hundred red deer. The number of deer in the park is controlled by a cull, it has been worked out that four hundred deer is the right number for the size of the park and the amount of food there. There are several lakes where people can go fishing. People are not allowed to go fishing without a fishing permit. Two park keepers look after the park with thirty Park Police Constables.
